      <abstract>
        <title>Abstract</title>
        <p>The prevalence of intravascular extension of bone sarcomas of the pelvis is unknown. We report a case of intravascular extension of an osteogenic sarcoma of the pelvis into the vena cava, correlating the pre-operative imaging findings with the intra-operative findings and specimen analysis. A brief review of the literature is provided.</p>
      </abstract>
